ZH: 他整天无所事事，连个工作也没找到。
EN: He is idle all day long, and haven't found a job yet.

ZH: 孩子们闲在家里无所事事，快出去玩吧。
EN: The kids are idle at home, go out and play.

ZH: 她从毕业后就待在家里无所事事。
EN: She has been idle at home since she graduated.

ZH: 我宁愿做点什么，也不想无所事事地度过每一天。
EN: I would rather do something than idle away every day.

ZH: 他们在度假村里无所事事地呆了一个星期。
EN: They stayed idle in the resort for a week.

ZH: 在这个城市，没有工作的人很容易无所事事地度日。
EN: In this city, people without jobs can easily idle away their days.

ZH: 她失业了，现在每天都无所事事地待在家里。
EN: She lost her job, now she stays idle at home every day.

ZH: 这个陌生人总是在公园里无所事事地乞讨。
EN: The stranger is always idling in the park begging for money.

ZH: 我很讨厌无所事事的感觉，我喜欢充实自己的生活。
EN: I hate the feeling of idleness, I prefer to live a fulfilling life.

ZH: 在养老院里，老人们总是无所事事地度过一整天。
EN: In the nursing home, the elderly always idle away their days.

ZH: 在家无所事事会让人变得无聊和懒散。
EN: Being idle at home can make a person bored and lazy.

ZH: 她觉得自己无所事事地浪费了好几个月。
EN: She felt like she wasted several months idly.

ZH: 年轻人应该充实自己的生活，不要一直无所事事。
EN: Young people should enrich their lives and not stay idle all the time.

ZH: 在工作之余，我喜欢做一些自己感兴趣的事情，不愿无所事事。
EN: In my spare time, I like to do things that interest me, rather than be idle.

ZH: 忙碌工作的人很少会无所事事，他们总是很充实。
EN: Busy people rarely idle away, they are always fulfilled.

ZH: 不要总是无所事事，多做些有意义的事情。
EN: Don't always idle away, do more meaningful things.

ZH: 上了年纪的人最怕无所事事，会容易生病。
EN: Elderly people are most afraid of idleness, as it can lead to illness.

ZH: 长时间无所事事可能会导致人变得沮丧和消极。
EN: Prolonged idleness can make people feel depressed and negative.

ZH: 他无所事事地坐在那里，看着时间一点点过去。
EN: He idly sat there, watching the time pass by.

ZH: 不要无所事事地浪费时间，抓住每一天的机会。
EN: Don't idle away your time, seize the opportunities of each day.
